2.Given a number n, find the value of n raised to the power of its own reverse.
Note: The result will always fit into a 32-bit signed integer.
Platform : GeeksforGeeks
SOURCE CODE :class Solution {
    public int reverseExponentiation(int n) {int rem=0;
       int num=n;  while(n>0){
          int rev=n%10;
       rem=rem*10+rev;
      
          n=n/10;}
        return (int)Math.pow(num,rem);
    }
}
